JOHANNESBURG Ratings agency Fitch has revised its view of the creditworthiness of five local banks. It s also amended its ratings for Eskom and MTN.This is line with its downgrade of the country's local and foreign currency debt last week.READ: Fitch downgrades SA to junk statusAbsa, FirstRand, Investec, Nedbank and Standard Bank are now rated at BB-plus or junk status.The ratings agency says South Africa's banks cannot have a higher sovereign rating than that of the country.eNCA